    "author_association": "MEMBER",
    "body": "Couple of thoughts here:\r\n\r\nWe have a bunch of components that allow consumers to create context menus. Namely:\r\n\r\n1. `StatusPopupMenu` (https://github.com/status-im/StatusQ/blob/master/src/StatusQ/Popups/StatusPopupMenu.qml)\r\n2. `StatusMenuItem` (https://github.com/status-im/StatusQ/blob/master/src/StatusQ/Popups/StatusMenuItem.qml)\r\n3. `StatusMenuItemDelegate` (https://github.com/status-im/StatusQ/blob/master/src/StatusQ/Popups/StatusMenuItemDelegate.qml) for more control\r\n4. `StatusMenuSeparator` (https://github.com/status-im/StatusQ/blob/master/src/StatusQ/Popups/StatusMenuSeparator.qml)\r\n\r\nWith these any context menu can already be implemented. It also supports nested menus.\r\n\r\nWhat is not \"supported\" out of the box, is an easy way to have this top most profile view item in the menu. \r\nFew things to do (1 is required, 2 is optional):\r\n\r\n1. Introduce a menu item component to render the profile information (top most item in the screenshot above). This could be a `StatusProfileMenuItem`. This one should most likely use things like `StatusSmartIdenticon` etc.\r\n2. Introduce a `StatusProfilePopupMenu` which essentially is a `StatusPopupMenu` in which the first item is always gonna be a `StatusProfileMenuItem`\r\n\r\nObviously, 2) is just a convenience composition and not necessarily needed. As soon as 1) is implemented, all of the above variants in the screenshot can be built using existing APIs.\r\n\r\nI'd like to see an API proposal for `StatusProfileMenuItem` here.",
